headlines.description: — Saddiq Bey scored 25 points, Cade Cunningham had 20 points and nine rebounds and the Detroit Pistons rallied to beat the Indiana Pacers 111-106 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham, Bey help Pistons rally past Pacers, 111-106

headlines.description: — James Harden is the new kid in town, earning raucous cheers from the moment he steps on the court. Joel Embiid hears wire-to-wire “MVP!” chants from Philly fans begging for a championship.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maxey-mum Effort: 76ers race past Cavs behind 33 from Maxey

headlines.description: — De'Andre Hunter scored 26 points and Trae Young added 25 to help the Atlanta Hawks beat the Washington Wizards 117-114 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hunter, Young help Hawks hold off Wizards 117-114

headlines.description: — Jrue Holiday hit enough big shots down the stretch while keeping DeMar DeRozan in check to help the Milwaukee Bucks squeeze out another tight win. And once again, they did it against a top Eastern Conference team.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 34 points, Bucks beat Bulls 118-112

headlines.description: — Cole Anthony had 15 points and 12 rebounds, Chuma Okeke had 10 points and a career-high 11 rebounds, and the Orlando Magic beat Toronto 103-97 on Friday night, snapping a nine-game losing streak against the Raptors.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic end 9-game skid against Raptors with 103-97 victory

events.name: Utah Jazz at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram scored 29 points and C.J. McCollum added 24 to power the New Orleans Pelicans to a 124-90 victory Friday night over the Utah Jazz.

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — The points are piling for the Minnesota Timberwolves, and so are the wins.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Reid score 20, lead Timberwolves past Thunder 138-101

headlines.description: — DeMarcus Cousins, starting in place of ailing Nikola Jokic, scored a season-high 31 points and the Denver Nuggets bounced back from a loss to beat the struggling Houston Rockets 116-101 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cousins leads in Jokic's absence, Nuggets beat Rockets

events.name: New York Knicks at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — New York's Julius Randle yelled at Phoenix's Cam Johnson, bumped chests with him and then shoved him again for good measure.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cam Johnson banks in 3, NBA-leading Suns stun Knicks 115-114
